"Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Eps","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["North German: topographic name for someone living on or owning land that was waterlogged or partly surrounded by water, from Middle Low German <i>es</i> ‘swamp, water’.","Swiss German: from the topographic name <i>Ess</i> ‘grazing area, pasture’.","Swiss German: from a vernacular short form of the personal name   Oswald  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Esse","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik.","Norwegian: habitational name from the farmstead Ese in Sogn of unexplained etymology, or Esse in Telemark, named with Old Norse <i>æsin</i> ‘hill’ + <i>-e</i> from <i>vin</i> ‘meadow’.","German: variant of   Ess  , or a topographic name from the river name Esse in Hesse."]},{"name":"Oswald","meanings":["Scottish (Fife and Lanarkshire), northern English, German, and French (mainly Alsace and Lorraine): from an Old English personal name composed of the elements <i>ōs</i> ‘god’ + <i>weald</i> ‘power’. In the Middle English period, this fell together with the less common Old Norse cognate <i>Ásvaldr</i>. The name was introduced to Germany from England, as a result of the fame of Saint Oswald, a 7th-century king of Northumbria, whose deeds were reported by Celtic missionaries to southern Germany. The name was also borne by a 10th-century English saint of Danish parentage, who was important as a monastic reformer. Veneration of Saint Oswald, the king, spread from the German lands to the neighbouring Slavic lands as well. The surname in the (German) spelling <i>Oswald</i> is thus also found especially in Czechia and Slovakia, while in North America it also absorbed various Slavic forms (see 3 below).","Irish (Down): adopted as an English equivalent of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> (see   Hussey   1).","Americanized form of Slovenian, Slovak, and Czech <b>Osvald</b>, Slovenian and Slovak <b>Ožvald</b> or <b>Ozvald</b>, and probably also of Slovenian <b>Ožbolt</b>: from vernacular forms of the German personal name <i>Oswald</i>, of Old English origin (see 1 above)."]}]},{"name":"Alan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Celtic origin and uncertain derivation (possibly a diminutive of a word meaning ‘rock’). It was introduced into England by  Breton  followers of  William the Conqueror , most notably  Alan , Earl of Brittany, who was rewarded for his services with vast estates in the newly conquered kingdom. In Britain the variants  <b>Allan</b>  and  <b>Allen</b>  are considerably less frequent, and generally represent transferred uses of surname forms, whereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alan Eps was born in 1425, in Brenzett, Kent, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1471, in his hometown, at the age of 46, and was buried in Kent, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1425–1471":"1425–1471","1457–1524":"1457–1524","1425":"1425","1524":"1524","1457":"1457","1471":"1471","Brenzett, Shepway District, Kent, England":"Brenzett, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St. Enswith Church, Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1425–1471":"1425–1471","1457–1524":"1457–1524","1425":"1425","1524":"1524","1457":"1457","1471":"1471","Brenzett, Shepway District, Kent, England":"Brenzett, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","St. Enswith Church, Kent, England":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1425–1471":"1425–1471","1457–1524":"1457–1524","1425":"1425","1524":"1524","1457":"1457","1471":"1471","Brenzett, Shepway District, Kent, England":"Brenzett, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","St. Enswith Church, Kent, England":"Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Alan Eps est né en 1425, à Brenzett, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1471, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 46 ans, et a été enterré à Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1425–1471":"1425–1471","1457–1524":"1457–1524","1425":"1425","1524":"1524","1457":"1457","1471":"1471","Brenzett, Shepway District, Kent, England":"Brenzett, Kent, England, United Kingdom","St. Enswith Church, Kent, England":"Kent, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Alan Eps wurde 1425 in Brenzett, Kent, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1471 im Alter von 46 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort und wurde in Kent, England, United Kingdom begraben."},"ht":{"1425–1471":"1425–1471","1457–1524":"1457–1524","1425":"1425","1524":"1524","1457":"1457","1471":"1471","Brenzett, Shepway District, Kent, England":"Brenzett, Kent, Angletè, United Kingdom","St. Enswith Church, Kent, England":"Kent, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1425–1471":"1425–1471","1457–1524":"1457–1524","1425":"1425","1524":"1524","1457":"1457","1471":"1471","Brenzett, Shepway District, Kent, England":"Brenzett, Kent, Anglia, United Kingdom","St. Enswith Church, Kent, England":"Kent, Anglia, United Kingdom"},"id":{"1425–1471":"1425–1471","1457–1524":"1457–1524","1425":"1425","1524":"1524","1457":"1457","1471":"1471","Brenzett, Shepway District, Kent, England":"Brenzett, Kent, Inggris, United Kingdom","St. Enswith Church, Kent, England":"Kent, Inggris, United Kingdom"},"it":{"1425–1471":"1425–1471","1457–1524":"1457–1524","1425":"1425","1524":"1524","1457":"1457","1471":"1471","Brenzett, Shepway District, Kent, England":"Brenzett, Kent, Inghilterra, Regno Unito","St. Enswith Church, Kent, England":"Kent, Inghilterra, Regno Unito","lifeSummary":"Alan Eps è nato il nel 1425 nel Brenzett, Kent, Inghilterra, Regno Unito. Lui avuto almeno 1 figlio. Morì nel 1471, nel sua cittadina, all'età di 46 anni, e fu sepolto a Kent, Inghilterra, Regno Unito."},"ja":{"1425–1471":"1425年–1471年","1457–1524":"1457年–1524年","1425":"1425年","1524":"1524年","1457":"1457年",